pull_request.title: fix(amf): Added Service Accept handling in case of Service Request with uplink data status
pull_request.body:
<!--
fix(amf): Added Service Accept handling in case of Service Request with uplink data status
-->

## Summary
Added Service Accept code In case If the Uplink data status IE is included in the Service Request message.


## Test Plan

Tested with Ue-Ran-Sim. 
Steps followed:
    -Bring up 5g call flow.
    -Restart Gnb.
## Additional Information
As per the 3gpp spec 24.501
If the Uplink data status IE is included in the SERVICE REQUEST message and the UE is: a) not in NB-N1 mode; or b) in NB-N1 mode and the UE does not indicate a request to have user-plane resources established for a number of PDU sessions that exceeds the UE's maximum number of supported user-plane resources; the AMF shall: a) indicate the SMF to re-establish the user-plane resources for the corresponding PDU sessions; b) include the PDU session reactivation result IE in the SERVICE ACCEPT message to indicate the user-plane resources re-establishment result of the PDU sessions for which the UE requested to re-establish the user-plane resources; and c) determine the UE presence in LADN service area and forward the UE presence in LADN service area towards the SMF, if the corresponding PDU session is a PDU session for LADN.

[Packet2610.zip](https://github.com/magma/magma/files/13174687/Packet2610.zip)

## Security Considerations

<!--
    Comment on potential security impact. Could the change create or 
    eliminate weaknesses? STRIDE, OWASP Top 10, or RFC 3552 may help.
-->

issue.title: Memory leak on services restart
issue.body:
Prior to submitting an issue, check to see if one has already been created. If there is currently an open issue, add a thumbs-up emoji to identify that it is also affecting you.

### Your Environment

- **Version: 1.8.0-1663094999-49ed2e69
- **Affected Component: AGW
- **Affected Subcomponent: AGW
- **Deployment Environment: VM AGW

### Describe the Issue

When making a change on Orch8rs wich require a services restart of AGW, the syslogs shown a Memory Leak message. This happens also on our bare metal AGW.

#### To Reproduce

Make any change that needs a service restart.

#### Additional context

Syslogs are here:

issue.title: fix(amf): Added Service Accept handling in case of Service Request with uplink data status

labels.name: size/S
labels.description: Denotes a PR that changes 10-29 lines.

issue.body:
<!--
fix(amf): Added Service Accept handling in case of Service Request with uplink data status
-->

## Summary
Added Service Accept code In case If the Uplink data status IE is included in the Service Request message.


## Test Plan

Tested with Ue-Ran-Sim
  -Bring up 5g call flow.
  -Restart Gnb.
## Additional Information
As per the 3gpp spec 24.501
If the Uplink data status IE is included in the SERVICE REQUEST message and the UE is: a) not in NB-N1 mode; or b) in NB-N1 mode and the UE does not indicate a request to have user-plane resources established for a number of PDU sessions that exceeds the UE's maximum number of supported user-plane resources; the AMF shall: a) indicate the SMF to re-establish the user-plane resources for the corresponding PDU sessions; b) include the PDU session reactivation result IE in the SERVICE ACCEPT message to indicate the user-plane resources re-establishment result of the PDU sessions for which the UE requested to re-establish the user-plane resources; and c) determine the UE presence in LADN service area and forward the UE presence in LADN service area towards the SMF, if the corresponding PDU session is a PDU session for LADN.

[Packet2610.zip](https://github.com/magma/magma/files/13174687/Packet2610.zip)

## Security Considerations

<!--
    Comment on potential security impact. Could the change create or 
    eliminate weaknesses? STRIDE, OWASP Top 10, or RFC 3552 may help.
-->

issue.title: Proposal: triage all SAST items
issue.body:
# Problem

There are a number of [code scanning alerts](https://github.com/magma/magma/security/code-scanning) that need to be looked at. It's slow work that has to be done because there are often issues found.

This is a blocker for https://github.com/magma/security/issues/152 and https://github.com/orgs/magma/projects/21/views/1

# Solution

1. Review every CodeQL alert
2. Fix the ones that make sense for me as an engineer
3. Create Engineering tickets for the ones that need somebody else

# Non-goals

Some of these will have negative ROI as a whole. The project isn't to fix every single little thing, it's to pay attention to every single thing and make sure something sensible is happening with it.

# Acceptance

The project will be complete when every alert has been triaged, every bit of engineering that I can do has a PR submitted, and there is an owner for every non-trivial item worth fixing.

# Bounty

I am asking for $2500.

issue.title: Migration towards new ASN compiler
issue.body:
### Problem

The current compiler used in Magma has several shortcomings and is occasionally unable to generate code capable of parsing messages sent by gNB  [#14125](https://github.com/magma/magma/pull/14125/) and  [#12846](https://github.com/magma/magma/issues/12846). Additionally, there are several other messages that failed to parse due to the compiler.

### Solution

In order to address the existing limitations and to overcome future obstacles, we are proposing a transition to a new compiler that includes pre-generated files for both 4G (S1-MME) and 5G (NGAP).

### Non-goals

Move towards new compiler

[Proposal link](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1e9LKnXrTXO7i4LfHbUYQoLMgprpwNW5-L7O3-voE0rw/edit)

labels.name: release-1.8-improvements
labels.description: Needs to be applied on issues reported on 1.8 Release builds

issue.body:
Prior to submitting an issue, check to see if one has already been created. If there is currently an open issue, add a thumbs-up emoji to identify that it is also affecting you.

### Your Environment

- **Version:** 1.8.0-1663094999-49ed2e69
- **Affected Component:** AGW
- **Affected Subcomponent:** sctpd
- **Deployment Environment:** Bare-metal (AGW)

### Describe the Issue

After being in normal operation SCTP service shows this log (syslog):
**sctpd[534043]: I1124 12:04:45.177053 534242 sctpd_uplink_client.cpp:55] sctpul.sendul error**

After a few minutes our BS (Huawei enb 3900) shows a mesage of SCTP link congestion.
This does not clears until we restart sctp services.
After an sctp service restart another error appears on logs:
**subscriberdb[246210]: ERROR:grpc._server:Exception calling application: database table is locked: subscriberdb
mobilityd[1458734]: .ERROR:grpc._server:Exception calling application: Unexpected internal state** 

This errors also provoke an state of sctp link congestion on enbs, it seems that S1 is not responding properly to enbs, timout occurs and enb send again the request and this keeps going like a snowball.

**_Something to notice is that this is not the first time to this to happend, all the times these errors have occurred has been when any enb has lost connection to AGW. Thats the only thing all events share in common._**

#### To Reproduce

1. Not sure how to reproduce as i have not been able to reproduce it on lab enviroment, i think it can be related to that in lab i have not so many users (production has about 200UE per AGW, have 2 AGW for a bout 450 UEs total).
